Unknown gunmen on Tuesday evening stormed Gudi, the ancestral home town of Governor Abdullahi Sule of Nasarawa State, in Akwanga Local Government Area, where they killed one person and abducted two persons (husband and wife). The victims are nephew and niece of the former Minister of Information, Mr Labaran Maku. The scene of the incident is not up 500 meters away from the railway and the Governor’s farm gate, where a detachment of Police officers are stationed. Our correspondent who visited the scene of the incident reported that the unknown gunmen stormed the residence of, Salisu Usman, immediate senior brother to Labaran Maku, along railway line in Gudi, around 8pm on Tuesday evening and shot sporadically, where they killed his daughter and took his son and wife to an unknown destination. The late Sa’adatu Usman, is a 400 level student of Usman Danfodio University Sokoto, while her senior brother Salisu Usman, who was kidnapped alongside the wife is an officer with the Nigeria Immigration Service (NIS), serving in Lafia. Father of the victims, ASP Salisu Usman (Rtd), who spoke to our correspondent said the house was besieged by the gunmen via fence who fired three shots at the Late Sa’adatu, through her room’s window and killed her. “I was on the dinning table eating when I heard the first gun shot, second shot then third, as a police officer, I concluded these are robbers, then shortly I heard my children screeming with their late sister in a pool of blood” “I quickly put a call to one of my friends who is also a retired police officer, but before the police came, they had killed my daughter and went away with my son who is an Immigration officer and his wife” Usman said. When contacted, Comptroller of Immigration in the state, Zainab Lawal, confirmed the incident. “Nigeria Immigration Officer, (NIS) Superintendent Salisu Usman and his wife have been abducted at gunpoint, while his sister was shot which led to her death” Lawal said.